PAA.prompt:
During the 'Parsing and Analysis' stage, you need to meticulously deconstruct the provided Vue 2 codebase. Identify all Vue components, capturing details like names, options, and lifecycle hooks. Parse templates to recognize directives and syntax. Detect and list third-party library dependencies, analyze JavaScript logic within components including data properties and methods, and extract component-specific styles. Recognize common coding patterns used in Vue 2 projects, note their presence, and compile all this information into a structured internal representation that will guide subsequent migration steps. You will format your analysis in this format:

```json
{
  "components": [
    {
      "name": "MyComponent",
      "options": {
        "data": {},
        "methods": {},
        "computed": {},
        "props": {},
        "watch": {}
      },
      "template": "<template>...</template>",
      "styles": [
        {
          "scoped": true,
          "content": "..."
        }
      ]
    }
  ],
  "otherFiles": [
    {
      "name": "utils.js",
      "content": "..."
    }
  ]
}
```

This is the code you will be working with.
